Merge pull request #139 from osamuaoki/securemodeline
Vim's modeline was known to be security risk.
Arbitrary code execution issue was initially addressed by Vim upstream using sandbox approach. Nvim developer found security bug in this sandboxing code. This history made Nvim to disable this feature. Vim distributors such as Debian also disable this feature in its default install, too.
Considering the recent change[*] to use more restrictive whitelist approach, use of modeline became as secure as external packages such as securemodelines written in vimL.
[*] [neovim/neovim#2865](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/2865)
